  "prompt": "Is Sri Ramakrishna Paramahamsa an avatar?",
  "response": "Sri Ramakrishna Paramahamsa is often considered an enlightened sage and spiritual teacher in Hinduism, particularly within the context of the Ramakrishna Order and the broader Vedantic tradition. While some followers and devotees regard him as an avatar or a divine incarnation due to his profound spiritual experiences and teachings, this belief can vary among different sects and individuals within Hinduism.\n\nIn Hindu philosophy, an avatar is often understood as a divine descent or manifestation of God in a physical form, primarily associated with deities like Vishnu. Ramakrishna himself emphasized the universal nature of spirituality and the unity of all religions, suggesting that while he might not fit into the traditional avatar concept of a specific deity, his life and teachings were nonetheless of great spiritual significance.\n\nUltimately, whether one views him as an avatar may depend on personal beliefs and interpretations within the context of Hindu theology.",
